5000|$|The Declaration was {{a source}} of {{contention}} during the subsequent alliance between the U.S., Great Britain, and the Soviet Union, but Welles persistently defended it. In a discussion with the media he asserted that the USSR had maneuvered to give [...] "an odor <b>of</b> <b>legality</b> to <b>acts</b> <b>of</b> aggression for purposes of the record".|$|R
