40|$|The {{administrative}} courts’ {{reform in}} Croatia has caused changes in special legislation. Important {{consequence of the}} reform is a different judicial control over local government acts. Under the current regulation, the Constitutional Court of the Republic of Croatia is competent for the control <b>of</b> constitutionality and <b>legality</b> <b>of</b> the local statutes, and High Administrative Court is the competent body for the review <b>of</b> the <b>legality</b> <b>of</b> general <b>acts</b> <b>of</b> local self-government. The paper also analyzes comparative solutions related {{to the issue of}} judicial review <b>of</b> general <b>acts</b> <b>of</b> local and regional government, especially French, German and Slovenian regulation...|$|R
